    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="683"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.30/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 5, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. My 186, September 4, noon. Yesterday at my request the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs promised to ask Minister of Gobierno at once for written statement of
                    charges against Sutton as well as permission for Embassy representative to
                    communicate with him, et cetera.</p>
                <p>If notification regarding charges not forthcoming shortly and Sutton is not
                    permitted to see Embassy representative and/or attorney, I believe the time will
                    have arrived when, recalling our patient attitude, we should protest vigorously
                    against what will then appear to be persecution rather than prosecution.</p>
                <p>I submit that the same should apply to Grow’s case if something is not done in
                    his regard within the next few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
